#. <section class="sutta" id="sn45.140"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn45.140:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 45"
msgstr "Linked Discourses 45"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "sn45.140:0.2"
msgid "11. Appamādapeyyālavagga"
msgstr "11. Abbreviated Texts on Diligence"

#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "sn45.140:0.3"
msgid "140. Padasutta"
msgstr "140. Footprints"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "sn45.140:1.1"
msgid ""
"“Seyyathāpi, bhikkhave, yāni kānici jaṅgalānaṃ pāṇānaṃ padajātāni, sabbāni "
"tāni hatthipade samodhānaṃ gacchanti;"
msgstr ""
"“The footprints of all creatures that walk can fit inside an elephant’s "
"footprint."

msgctxt "sn45.140:1.2"
msgid "hatthipadaṃ tesaṃ aggamakkhāyati, yadidaṃ—mahantattena;"
msgstr "So an elephant’s footprint is said to be the biggest of them all."

msgctxt "sn45.140:1.3"
msgid ""
"evameva kho, bhikkhave, ye keci kusalā dhammā, sabbe te appamādamūlakā "
"appamādasamosaraṇā; appamādo tesaṃ dhammānaṃ aggamakkhāyati."
msgstr ""
"In the same way, all skillful qualities are rooted in diligence and meet at "
"diligence, and diligence is said to be the best of them."

msgctxt "sn45.140:1.4"
msgid ""
"Appamattassetaṃ, bhikkhave, bhikkhuno pāṭikaṅkhaṃ—ariyaṃ aṭṭhaṅgikaṃ maggaṃ "
"bhāvessati ariyaṃ aṭṭhaṅgikaṃ maggaṃ bahulīkarissati."
msgstr ""
"A mendicant who is diligent can expect to develop and cultivate the noble "
"eightfold path."

msgctxt "sn45.140:1.5"
msgid ""
"Kathañca, bhikkhave, bhikkhu appamatto ariyaṃ aṭṭhaṅgikaṃ maggaṃ bhāveti "
"ariyaṃ aṭṭhaṅgikaṃ maggaṃ bahulīkaroti?"
msgstr ""
"And how does a mendicant who is diligent develop and cultivate the noble "
"eightfold path?"

msgctxt "sn45.140:1.6"
msgid ""
"Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu sammādiṭṭhiṃ bhāveti vivekanissitaṃ virāganissitaṃ "
"nirodhanissitaṃ vossaggapariṇāmiṃ … pe … sammāsamādhiṃ bhāveti "
"vivekanissitaṃ virāganissitaṃ nirodhanissitaṃ vossaggapariṇāmiṃ …"
msgstr ""
"It’s when a mendicant develops right view, right thought, right speech, "
"right action, right livelihood, right effort, right mindfulness, and right "
"immersion, which rely on seclusion, fading away, and cessation, and ripen as "
"letting go. …"

msgctxt "sn45.140:1.7"
msgid ""
"evaṃ kho, bhikkhave, bhikkhu appamatto ariyaṃ aṭṭhaṅgikaṃ maggaṃ bhāveti "
"ariyaṃ aṭṭhaṅgikaṃ maggaṃ bahulīkarotī”ti."
msgstr ""
"That’s how a mendicant who is diligent develops and cultivates the noble "
"eightfold path.”"

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn45.140:1.8"
msgid "Dutiyaṃ."
msgstr ""
